                            <comment id="12950972" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 25 Feb 2009 07:18:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Roman please also change the header key to the new CamelCase syntax for the 2.x commit. You can look at samples on the Exchange interface in 2.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12950959" author="romkal" created="Wed, 25 Feb 2009 15:33:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Used exchange property to store the exception. Property name is Exchange.EXCEPTION_CAUGHT constant.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committed only to 2.0.0 as it completely changes the behavior of exception handling. If someone had code depending on &quot;caught.exception&quot; header it will break.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
